# FlowTyme server rules

## Service boundaries (prefer extending these)

- Routes are thin: validate inputs, call services, return typed JSON.
- `services/notion-parser.ts`: Notion Blocks traversal (remember: children are not auto-recursed).
- `services/slot-finder.ts`: 15-minute step search; conflicts are flagged, not silently fixed.
- `services/caldav.ts`: iCloud read/write via `tsdav` + `ical.js`.
- Config and proposals persist in MongoDB (no filesystem config).

## Critical invariants

- Never store iCloud/Notion credentials in MongoDB (Phase 1). They belong in `server/.env`.
- Column 3 “partition hints”: if a col-3 item matches an existing Apple Calendar event name, ignore it (avoid duplicates).
- If an item is conflicting, keep it visible (fallback slot is OK), but default `accepted` to false.

## CalDAV gotcha

- `DAVCalendar.displayName` may be `string | Record<string, unknown>`. Use `String(cal.displayName || 'Unknown')`.

